Real-world enterprise architecture
Users
   │
Route 53
   │
CloudFront
   │
Application Load Balancer
   │
Auto Scaling Group (EC2)
   │
Apache + Node.js Application
   │
Amazon EFS (shared uploads)
   │
Amazon RDS (MySQL/PostgreSQL)
   │
Amazon S3 (backups/static assets)

Monitoring:
CloudWatch → Alarms → Lambda → SNS Notifications

Automation:
Python (Boto3)
Node.js (AWS SDK)
AWS CLI (Bash)
Notes
Python is the most widely used language for AWS automation because of the mature Boto3 SDK and extensive ecosystem.
Node.js is commonly used for serverless functions, REST APIs, and backend services using the AWS SDK for JavaScript.
Apache HTTP Server is a web server configured with configuration files (httpd.conf, virtual host files), not a scripting language. It serves web content and can reverse-proxy requests to applications written in Node.js, Python, Java, or other languages.
Bash + AWS CLI remains a standard choice for deployment scripts, instance bootstrap (user-data), and CI/CD pipelines.    
